# harness.yaml.example — canonical reference configuration.
#
# This file is the SOURCE OF TRUTH for what a valid harness.yaml looks like.
# If a new feature can't be expressed here, reconsider whether it belongs in
# the harness at all (see CLAUDE.md §7).
#
# CONTENTS
#   - One section per pluggable concern: scanners, policy, audit_sinks,
#     tool_registry, secrets.
#   - Each adapter is referenced by NAME (the entry-point name), not by
#     import path. The discovery layer (adapters/discovery.py) resolves
#     names to classes at startup.
#   - Boundary-level toggles: scan_input.enabled, scan_output.enabled.
#     check_tool_call has no toggle — it is mandatory.
#
# WHAT THE CODING AGENT SHOULD DO HERE
#   Fill in concrete YAML demonstrating every reference adapter. Use
#   ${ENV_VAR} interpolation in at least one place to show config/resolution
#   is wired. Use a secret reference (secret://name) in at least one place
#   to show SecretsProvider is wired.
#
# DO NOT
#   - Reference enterprise adapter names (purview, opa, splunk) here. The
#     example must work with only `pip install harness`.
#   - Add settings that have no consumer in the codebase. Every key must
#     map to a field in config/schema.py.
